column3:
{pageend:Po-Po-Pokémon!}
I want to become more like a Pikachu! Will you
battle me?

If you boot up TM10, you can use it to teach
{pageend:Work Up to a Pokémon.}
A Pokémon that uses Work Up in battle will raise
{pageend:its Attack and Sp. Atk at the same time.}
But remember—a TM is good for one use only.
Don’t waste it!

{pageend:I just became friends with my Pokémon.}
I’m not sure if we can do this properly, but may
we battle?

{pageend:Boo! Where’s your sense of adventure?}
Don’t be shy about talking to people and getting
into battles!

{pageend:Before we make our toast, I’d hoped for a battle.}
However, you seem to be short a Pokémon
for that.

{pageend:There is no price too high for the sake of my art.}
That said... My oh my, these meals look
awfully pricey...

The worth of a meal isn’t determined merely
{pageend:by its flavor.}
Presentation—that is, color and placement—
{pageend:is vital.}
In other words, a fine meal can be likened to the
finest work of art...

Gourmet dining in restaurants and exhilarating
{pageend:Pokémon battles...}
There is so much contentment in my life!

{pageend:Mmm, this sauce!}
It’s a spicy sauce made Hoenn-style from grated
Cheri Berries!

{pageend:My wallet’s empty after paying the prize money...}
Oh, no, it’s OK! No need to worry! I still have my
secret stash of cash!

I’m willing to have a battle with my son,
{pageend:my pride and joy.}
But you must bring more Pokémon than that.

{pageend:I’m no cook. I’ll admit that freely.}
But battling Pokémon... There’s something I’m
comfortable with.

Do you think we should rehearse this one
{pageend:more time?}
Today’s featured drink is freshly squeezed...

{pageend:Please don’t talk to me while we’re filming!}
Oh, actually, hold on. A Trainer barges in on our
{pageend:fine dining experience...}
I like that! It adds drama to our story!

Do you know what the most important thing is
{pageend:for gourmet reporting?}
It’s a...thesaurus-like vocabulary!

{pageend:My boyfriend’s a stock market wizard!}
Did you know? Someone who’s that lucky also
{pageend:happens to make for a tough Trainer.}
Are you willing to try your luck against that?

If I had the power of premonition, I’d be a terror
{pageend:on the markets.}
But you know that’s not really possible.

How can you guess right about everything all
{pageend:the time?}
Do you really have the power of premonition?

{pageend:Oh, dear! I wish you wouldn’t!}
We’re at a fancy restaurant, and you want to
analyze what’s served?

My husband never ceases to amaze me with his
{pageend:dedication to research.}
Would you care to have a battle with us?

A Technical Machine, or TM for short,
{pageend:contains a Pokémon move.}
Using a TM, you can instantly teach
{pageend:its move to a Pokémon.}
You’ll find you receive lots of copies
{pageend:of a TM when you obtain it.}
Don’t be shy to use them!
